    <div class="field">
      <%= f.label :focus %> &nbsp;
      <% if @select_focus == true %>
        <%= select( :objective, :focus, Objective::FOCUS_TYPES, 
                         :prompt => true) %>
      <% else %>
        <%= @objective.focus_name.upcase %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    
    <div class="field">
      <%= f.label :objective %> &nbsp; <span id="info", style ="cursor:help"><%= image_tag("info.png", :size => "20x20") %></span><br />
      
      <div id="infotext" class="info_box_screen" style = "margin-left:0; margin-right: 150px; display:none">
        In each of the focus areas (Profit, Customers, Employees and Processes) add up to 5 key objectives for the
        coming months.  For example, in Customers, you might include <i>'Increase direct sales by improving the company website'</i>.
        <br /></br />
        Review your business objectives at least every 6 months, and bring them up to date as circumstances change.
        &nbsp; <span id = "no-info" style="color:#069; cursor:n-resize">(Hide)</span>
      </div>
      
      <%= f.text_area :objective, :cols => 60, :rows => 3 %>
      <span id="char-count-objective" style = "color:blue; padding-left: 5px"><%= @characters_objective %></span>
    </div>

    

    <div class="field">
      <%= f.label :measurement %> &nbsp; <span id="info2", style ="cursor:help"><%= image_tag("info.png", :size => "20x20") %></span><br />
      
      <div id="infotext2" class="info_box_screen" style = "margin-left:0; margin-right: 150px; display:none">
        
        Describe how and when you're going to measure success.  For example, if the objective is to increase direct sales via the website,e the
        measurement might be <i>'At least 500 website-generated sales worth Â£50,000 by December 31'.</i>
        <br /><br />
        Again, review the statements frequently to take account of new circumstances.  If you've achieved the current targets, set them 
        higher next time.
        &nbsp; <span id = "no-info2" style="color:#069; cursor:n-resize">(Hide)</span>
      </div>
      
      <%= f.text_area :measurement, :cols => 60, :rows => 3 %>
      <span id="char-count-measurement" style = "color:blue; padding-left: 5px"><%= @characters_measurement %></span>
    </div>
    
<% content_for :javascript do %>

  <%= javascript_tag do %>
    
   $(document).ready(function(){
    
    $('#info').click(function() {
      $('#infotext').show('fast', function() {
      });
    });
    
    $('#info2').click(function() {
      $('#infotext2').show('fast', function() {
      });
    });
    
    $('#no-info').click(function() {
      $('#infotext').hide('fast', function() {
      });
    });
    
    $('#no-info2').click(function() {
      $('#infotext2').hide('fast', function() {
      });
    });
    
    $('#objective_objective').live('keyup keydown', function(e) {
    var maxLen = 255;
    var left = maxLen - $(this).val().length;
    $('#char-count-objective').html(left);
    });
    
    $('#objective_measurement').live('keyup keydown', function(e) {
    var maxLen = 255;
    var left = maxLen - $(this).val().length;
    $('#char-count-measurement').html(left);
    });
    
   });
   
  <% end %>
<% end %>
